theorem Topology.interior_sUnion_eq_sUnion_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (F : Set (Set X)) (hF : ∀ A : Set X, A ∈ F → IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    interior (⋃₀ F : Set X) = ⋃₀ F := by
  -- The union of any collection of open sets is open.
  have h_open : IsOpen (⋃₀ F : Set X) := by
    refine IsOpen.sUnion ?_
    intro A hA
    exact hF A hA
  -- For an open set `U`, `interior U = U`.
  simpa [h_open.interior_eq]

theorem IsOpen.sUnion {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {F : Set (Set X)}
    (hF : ∀ A : Set X, A ∈ F → IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    IsOpen (⋃₀ F : Set X) := by
  simpa using isOpen_sUnion (X := X) hF
